{
  "texts": [
    "This was the major shift in the life strategy of early humans (Jordania, 2014 (Jordania,, 2017;; Somerville, 2019).",
    "Although early humans at first avoided lions, their natural predators, later, after finetuning their audio-visual-olfactory intimidating display (AVOID), they started attacking and chasing lions off after the kill was made.",
    "So, instead of avoiding lions, early humans started searching (and following) lions.",
    "Humans became active \"vulture-searchers\" in order to know about the scavenging opportunities on the open savannah.",
    "This must have been the final step away from the patches of trees to open terrain."
  ]
}